summary: An Ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 23781, entitled "An Ordinance authorizing the Mayor and City Comptroller to issue Local Improvement Bonds for the improvement of East Seventieth Street from Fifth Avenue Northeast to Tenth Avenue Northeast, et al, in the City of Seattle by grading, etc, under Ordinance No. 20408, creating Local Improvement District No. 2003, prescribing the rate of interest thereon and authorizing their delivery to the contractor constructing the improvement," approved April 7, 1910.
